steps:
Grow Symbiodinium cells
1. Grow Symbiodinium cells in IMK or IMK+casein hydrolysate medium to mid log phase, the concentration is about 106 cells/mL.

Harvest Symbiodinium cells
2. Spin down the cells at 1000 g at room temperature for 5 minutes, and remove the supernatant.

Prepare the lysis buffer
3. Warm up the 2X lysis buffer if precipitated. Dilute the buffer using equal volume of water, and make it into 1X lysis buffer.
NOTES Approximately 500 µl of lysis buffer is needed for 1 million cells. Prepare the appropriate amount of lysis buffer based on the numer of samples for processing.

Lyse Symbiodinium cells
4. Add the 500 µl 1X lysis buffer to the cell pellet;
5. Vortex the pellet to resuspend it well at room temperature.
6. Add 500 µl Phenol:Chloroform:Isoamyl alcohol (25:24:1) to the lysis buffer, and mix well by inverting for a few times.
7. Separate phases by centrifugation at 13,000 g for 5 minutes, and transfer the upper layer which contains the DNA to a new 1.5 mL eppendorf tube.

RNaseA treatment to get rid of RNA
8. Treat the supernatant with 4 µl Ribonuclease A (20mg/mL), and incubate the solution for 30 minutes at 37°C.

Purify the DNA - get rid of the proteins
9. Add 500 µl Phenol:Chloroform:Isoamyl alcohol (25:24:1) to the solution and mix well by inverting for a few times;NOTES Make sure get clean upper layer from this extraction, do not touch the middle layer. Extract withChloroform:Isoamyl alcohol (24:1) for additional times if needed to fully get rid of proteins.
10. Separate phases by centrifugation at 13,000 g at room temperature for 5 min;
11. Transfer the upper layer phase to a new 1.5 mL eppendorf tube;
12. Add 500 µl Chloroform:Isoamyl alcohol (24:1) to the solution and mix well by inverting a few times;
13. Separate phases by centrifugation at 13,000 g at room temperature for 5 min;
14. Tranfer the upper layer phase to a new 1.5 mL eppendorf tube.

Precipitate the DNA
15. Add 2.5 volumes of absolute Ethanol, incubate on ice for 30 min or at -20 ºC overnight;
16. Centrifuge the solution at 13,000 g at room temperature for 20 minutes;
17. Wash the pellet once with 1mL of 70% Ethanol;
18. Dry the pellet and resupsend in 50 µl H2O;
19. Quantify the DNA concentration by NanoDrop, and run a small amount (for example 1 µl) on 1% agrose gel.
NOTES Agarose gel electrophoresis of Symbiodinium genomic DNA obtained using this protocol. ?
